**Additional Information:** When sending an HTTP request with a loopback address and an improper port, the following HTTP response was returned.

Request:
```http
GET http://127.0.0.1:81/ HTTP/1.1


```

Response:
```http
HTTP/1.1 301 Moved Permanently
Server: BlueCoat-Security-Appliance
Location:http://███████
Connection: Close

<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Redirection</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><H1>Redirect</H1></BODY>
```

In addition, I found the following file.

Request:
```http
GET http://████████/proxy_pac_file HTTP/1.1


```

Response:
```http
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Server: BlueCoat-Security-Appliance
Content-Type: application/x-ns-proxy-autoconfig
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
Date: Sun, 19 Feb 2017 02:02:55 GMT
Cache-Control: private, no-cache, no-store, max-age=0
Connection: close
Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
X-Frame-Options: sameorigin

function FindProxyForURL(url, host)
{
	if( url.substring(0, 5) == "http:" )
	{
		return "PROXY █████████:8080; DIRECT";
	}
	else if( url.substring(0, 6) == "https:" )
	{
		return "PROXY ████:8080; DIRECT";
	}
	else if( url.substring(0, 4) == "ftp:" )
	{
		return "PROXY ████████:8080; DIRECT";
	}
	else
	{
		return "DIRECT";
	}
}
```

ProxySG seems to be running in front of the web server due to the presence of Server header and config file. Since it may be useful for identifying the cause, I will report it additionally.

Also, during this inspection, connections from my IP address are now refused.

Since I'm not aiming at network intrusion, I will not explore this vulnerability anymore. However, since there are other vulnerabilities to report on the SSI website, I still need to access this website.

Would you please exclude [my IP address](https://hackerone.com/reports/198218#activity-1419480) from the blacklist?

Your help would be appreciated.
